Three Kiambu County government officials arrested over the alleged embezzlement of public funds worth Ksh. 588 million are being held at integrity center, the EACC headquarters here in Nairobi. The three include a company director, Charles Chege, and two members of the tender evaluation board, Joyce Ngina, and Simon Kang'ethe. Kiambu governor Ferdinand Waititu has also been asked to present himself at the EACC headquarters immediately, following Friday's public arrest warrant for the governor and nine other suspects.